Segun Awofadeji in Bauchi The Speaker of House of Representatives, Hon. Yakubu Dogara has sponsored free medical treatment to 10, 000 people in Bauchi Local Government Area, Bauchi State on various ailments. The medical outreach which commenced on yesterday at Abubakar Tafawa Balewa University Teaching Hospital (ATBUTH) Bauchi would be carried out by specialists under the aegis of ‘Doctors on the Move Africa. Speaking with Journalists shortly after the flag off of the exercise, team leader of Doctors on the Move Africa, Dr. Haruna Joseph Kigbu said this edition “is the first phase of the annual free medical outreach being sponsored by the speaker. He added that the second phase would hold in Azare, Katagum Local Government Area of the state. ‘’We are here today, to implement a free medical outreach program that is being sponsored by the Speaker of the Nigerian Parliament Yakubu Dogara. Our projection for the next six days is treat about 10, 000 patients. Last time, we were able to treat 18, 000 patients in this hospital. “The services to be provided to patients include general consultation, administration of free drugs, laboratory service, ultrasound scanning, test and treatment of diabetes, hyper tension and surgery on people with cataracts, fibroids, Hernia etc. He urged the Bauchi State Governor-elect, Senator Bala Mohammed to commit funds into such project opining that many people die of ailments because they cannot afford health services. One of the beneficiaries, Laraba Shehu said she was there to receive treatment on her hyper tension, commending Dogara for the gesture confessing that he brought succour to patients that are poor.